# FitLit crontab — keep the orchestrator running.
#
# crontab can't tick faster than once a minute, so the *orchestrator* owns the
# 10-second cadence and per-fetcher scheduling. cron's only job is to make sure
# the orchestrator process is alive.
#
# Replace /absolute/path/to/FitLit before installing.
#
# --- Option A (recommended): start once at boot, let it loop forever ----------
@reboot cd /absolute/path/to/FitLit && /usr/bin/env uv run python -m fitlit.orchestrator >> data/state/orchestrator.log 2>&1

# --- Option B: minute-cron watchdog --------------------------------------------
# If you'd rather not run a long-lived daemon, run a single dispatch tick every
# minute instead (coarser than 10s, but pure cron). Comment out Option A and use:
# * * * * * cd /absolute/path/to/FitLit && /usr/bin/env uv run python -m fitlit.orchestrator --once >> data/state/orchestrator.log 2>&1
